Install Ansible on Master 
sudo apt update
sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible
sudo apt install ansible –y
ansible –version

ssh-keygen
cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub

ssh ubuntu@<public-ip-address of Slave>

sudo vi /etc/ansible/hosts
[remote-hosts]
ansibleslave ansible_host= public ip of slave

 ansible -m ping ansibleslave
ansible -m ping remote-hosts (Now, we have verified that Ansible Master and Slave can respond to Ansible SSH connection through inventory file “hosts”)




 
